<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1062903-anyone-else-pick-up-on-the-protagonist-s">Anyone else pick up on the protagonist&#39;s sexism? I can&#39;t figure out if it was purposely meant to make the character unlikeable, or if Crichton was actually pretty sexist back in 1968.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1062903'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F7663.A_Case_of_Need">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1062903-anyone-else-pick-up-on-the-protagonist-s">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1062903-anyone-else-pick-up-on-the-protagonist-s">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/62409560-chieftb"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/62409560-chieftb">Chieftb</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This book is incredibly dated and reflects the culture of 1968. Yes, it is sexist...note there are no women doctors...None...and the nurses and all wo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This book is incredibly dated and reflects the culture of 1968. Yes, it is sexist...note there are no women doctors...None...and the nurses and all women are sexualized. There was no HIPPA and no patient protection at all. The medicine itself is out of date compared to today’s standards. Autopsies are barely done anymore unless it is a major homicide. And using a “rabbit test” for pregnancy is like bloodletting. As a woman physician, I could barely stand reading it. But it certainly did reflect the times. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

