<span id="freeTextContainer10547687576142388059">I&apos;ve always liked Michael Crichton&apos;s novels, and I had missed this one. It was perhaps more interesting to me now than it would have been in 1968 when it was published in the pre-Roe v. Wade days of illegal abortion. It feels a little dated in spots; for example, the respectful word for African-Americans was still Negro. Otherwise, it&apos;s a good, fast-paced mystery with characteristic Crichton-esque twists and turns.</span>
  <span id="freeText10547687576142388059" style="display:none">I've always liked Michael Crichton's novels, and I had missed this one. It was perhaps more interesting to me now than it would have been in 1968 when it was published in the pre-Roe v. Wade days of illegal abortion. It feels a little dated in spots; for example, the respectful word for African-Americans was still Negro. Otherwise, it's a good, fast-paced mystery with characteristic Crichton-esque twists and turns.</span>
